| image      = [[File:CoA_Empire_of_Brazil_(1847-1889).svg|55px|alt=Coat of arms consisting of a shield with a green field with a golden armillary sphere over the red and white Cross of the Order of Christ, surrounded by a blue band with 20 silver stars; the bearers are two arms of a wreath, with a coffee branch on the left and a flowering tobacco branch on the right; and above the shield is an arched golden and jeweled crown]]
| royal name = Teresa Cristina, Empress of Brazil
| dipstyle   = [[Imperial Majesty (style)|Her Imperial Majesty]]
| offstyle   = Your Imperial Majesty
| altstyle   = Ma'am
}}

=== Titles and styles ===

* '''14 March 1822&amp;nbsp;– 30 May 1843''': ''Her Royal Highness'' The ''Most Serene'' Princess ''Donna'' Teresa Cristina of the Two Sicilies
* '''30 May 1843&amp;nbsp;– 15 November 1889''': ''Her Imperial Majesty'' The Empress

The Empress' full style and title were &quot;Her Imperial Majesty Dona Teresa Cristina, Empress of Brazil&quot;.

=== Foreign honors ===

* Band of the Spanish [[Order of Queen Maria Luisa]].{{sfn|Sauer|1889|p=42}}
* Band of the Portuguese [[Order of Saint Isabel]].{{sfn|Sauer|1889|p=42}}
* Insignia of the Austrian [[Order of the Starry Cross]].{{sfn|Sauer|1889|p=42}}
* Insignia of the Bavarian [[Order of Saint Elizabeth]].{{sfn|Sauer|1889|p=42}}
* Grand Cross of the [[Order of the Holy Sepulchre]].{{sfn|Sauer|1889|p=42}}
* Grand Dame of Honour and Devotion of the [[Sovereign Military Order of Malta|Order of Malta]].{{sfn|Sauer|1889|p=42}}

